<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>He has spoken at length about his troubled childhood and working tirelessly to achieve his success.</p>

<p>And in an awkward misunderstanding, Machine Gun Kelly appeared rather offended after what was meant to be a glowing introduction by radio hosts Kyle Sandilands and Jackie 'O' Henderson on their breakfast show on Wednesday.</p>

<p>The American rapper, 30, accused Kyle of claiming he was 'born with a silver spoon in his mouth', when in fact Kyle, 49, had been joking about his co-host Jackie's 'rich' upbringing.</p>

<p>Scroll down for video    </p>

<p>'Are you being facetious?' Machine Gun Kelly, 30, appeared offended following what was meant to be his glowing introduction by Kyle Sandilands and Jackie 'O' Henderson on their radio show on Wednesday</p>

<p>Kyle said of the hitmaker, whose real name is Colson Baker, during the introduction: 'This kid, he brought himself up.'</p>

<p>Speaking to Jackie, he added: 'You know, how you got brought up by your very rich parents, and you had the silver spoon up your a******* your whole life.</p>

<p>'Then here's kids like me who brought themselves up because our parents didn't want us. And that's Machine Gun Kelly. The guy is a worldwide success!'</p>

<p>There was a long pause before Machine, who was on the line from the United States, coldly asked: 'Are you being facetious right now?'</p>

<p>Misunderstanding: The American rapper accused Kyle of claiming he was born with a silver spoon in the mouth, when in fact the 50-year-old was joking about his co-host Jackie's 'rich' upbringing</p>

<p>Kyle related to the hitmaker during the introduction, saying: 'This kid, he brought himself up.' Speaking to Jackie, he added: 'You know, how you got brought up by your very rich parents'</p>

<p>Responded to the star's claims he was being flippant about his tough upbringing, Kyle said: 'No, no! I brought myself up. I was a homeless teenager here in Australia, and I know what it's like.'</p>

<p>There was another long pause before the Bad Things rapper realised he had misheard Kyle.</p>

<p>'Oh, I'm sorry! I thought you were referring to me. I thought you said I had a silver spoon in my mouth!' the mortified star explained.</p>

<p>A horrified Jackie replied: 'Oh my God! He was referring to me!'</p>

<p>Elsewhere in the conversation, the loved-up star kept coy on his romance with actress, Megan Fox.</p>

<p>Misheard: There was a long pause before Machine, who was on the line from the United States, coldly asked: 'Are you being facetious right now?' Pictured at 2020 MTV Video Music Awards in August</p>

<p>A horrified Jackie replied: 'Oh my God! He was referring to me!'</p>

<p>However, he did make it clear that his new relationship with Megan meant he wouldn't be entertaining any admirers when Kyle informed him that his employees were delighted upon learning he would be on the show.</p>

<p>Machine and Megan went public with their romance in May, after meeting on the set of the movie Midnight In The Switchgrass.</p>

<p>Megan was previously married to former Beverly Hills, 90210 star Brian Austin Green, 47.  </p>

<p>The former couple began dating after meeting on the set of a TV sitcom in 2004. Following an on-off-on again engagement, they tied the knot in 2010.</p>

<p>Megan and the Beverly Hills, 90210 star share sons Noah, eight, Bodhi, six, and Journey, four.</p>

